From: proton-carddav-sync patch
Subject: [PATCH] fix address.go: update slices.SortFunc callback to Go 1.21 int-return signature

Go 1.21 changed slices.SortFunc to require a comparison function that
returns int (cmp-style: negative/zero/positive) instead of bool.
go-proton-api v0.4.0 ships the old bool-returning form which causes a
build failure with Go 1.21+.

This patch replaces the bool-returning lambda with a cmp.Compare call,
matching what upstream already does on its default branch.

Apply with:
  cd $(go env GOMODCACHE)/github.com/!proton!mail/go-proton-api@v0.4.0
  chmod -R u+w .
  patch -p1 < /path/to/patches/go-proton-api-address-sortfunc.patch

Or use the gomod-replace workaround in go.mod (see README).
---
--- a/address.go
+++ b/address.go
@@ -1,9 +1,10 @@
 package proton
 
 import (
+	"cmp"
 	"context"
 
-	"golang.org/x/exp/slices"
+	"slices"
 
 	"github.com/go-resty/resty/v2"
 )
@@ -18,8 +19,8 @@ func (c *Client) GetAddresses(ctx context.Context) ([]Address, error) {
 	}); err != nil {
 		return nil, err
 	}
 
-	slices.SortFunc(res.Addresses, func(a, b Address) bool {
-		return a.Order < b.Order
+	slices.SortFunc(res.Addresses, func(a, b Address) int {
+		return cmp.Compare(a.Order, b.Order)
 	})
 
 	return res.Addresses, nil
